<h2><a name = "Newadd"> Announcing a New Addition to the Bora Laskin Law Library World Wide Web Home Page </a></h2></center>
<p> 
<H3>by Anne Johnston, World Wide Web Technician</h3>
<p>
The Bora Laskin Law Library has recently added an  &quot;Alphabetical Listing of  Electronic Law Journals&quot: to its home page (URL=<a href="http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca/resources/journals.htm">http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca/resources/journals.htm)</a>.  It lists the law journals currently available on Lexis, QuickLaw and Westlaw, as well as those on the Internet that are available in full-text format. The list also includes holdings information where available and the Lexis file name or the Westlaw database identifier code to facilitate access to these journals in their respective databases.  
<p>
While many journals have home pages on the Internet, only a few provide access to actual full-text articles. For that reason very few links have been made to Internet sources for journals.  However, links will be added and updated as more full-text journals become available.
<p>
In addition, the list provides hypertext links to the Lexis, QuickLaw and Westlaw home pages. Through these home pages you can retrieve information on how to get passwords for each of these databases and how to connect to them  via the Internet. 





