<img align = left src = "../icons/libgry5.gif"><center><h1><cite>LawLink</cite></h1>
<h3>The Newsletter of the Bora Laskin Law Library<br>

University of Toronto</h3><p>
<a href = "http://www.law-lib.utoronto.ca">[Bora Laskin Law Library]</a> <a href = "http://www.utoronto.ca/">[University of Toronto]</a></center>
<br clear = "all">
<p><center><img src = "../icons/grkban09.gif"></center><p>
<h3>January 1996, Volume 2 Number 4</h3>

<h2>Contents</h2>
<dl>
<dd><a href = "v2n4.htm #website"> Interesting Internet Sites. An Annotated Review of the &quot;World Wide Web Virtual Library: Law&quot; </a></h2></center>

</dl>
<p>
<center><img src = "../icons/grkban09.gif"><p>
<h2><a name = "website"> Interesting Internet Sites. An Annotated Review of the &quot;World Wide Web Virtual Library: Law&quot;</a></h2></center>

<h3><center>by Susan Barker</h3></Center>


The &quot;World Wide Web Virtual Library: Law &quot; URL=<a href="http://www.law.indiana.ed:80/law/lawindex.html">(http://www.law.indiana.edu:80/law/lawindex.html)</a> is a comprehensive list of legal resources on the Internet.  Through this site you can locate or find  information on: U.S immigration for Canadian businesses and professionals,  SEC  filings, the constitutions of various countries and peoples, the Gatt, a variety of law publishers, the Lexis/Nexis Communication Center as well as a huge amount of other law- related information.  Although the majority of the links are to American sources, there are links to British, Canadian, Australian and  international law sites.
 <p>
The following  is an annotated and edited compilation of the contents of the &quot;World Wide Web Virtual Library: Law"&quot; site. Some of  the annotations  have been provided by the  &quot; World Wide Web Virtual Library: Law &quot;; the rest have been supplied by the author.  Links on the site which are strictly commercial have been omitted as have sites  that no longer have a valid URL. As with all Internet sites, please be aware that the Web changes daily;  some of these links may no longer be current  and other  interesting sites may have been added. 
<br>
<h3>Topical Organizations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Material Organized by Legal Topic (Constitutional Law, Copyright ... From the Legal Information Institute, Cornell 	University)
<li>Material Organized by Type or Source  (Treaty, Legislation ... From the Legal  Information Insitute, Cornell University)
<li>Chicago-Kent's Guide to Legal Resources
<li>Law and Regulations from EINet Galaxy
<li>P-Law Legal Resource Locator
	Updated to February 1995.
<li>Yahoo - Law
<li>Topical Index for Law from EINet Galaxy
<li>Law-on-the-WEB Master Index
<li>Legal Resource Network
<li>The Seamless Web - Law
<li>Neopolis Law Resource Center
<li>Emory Law Library Electronic Reference Desk
</ul>
