<h2><a name = "can2">Canadian Legal Resources Available on the Internet: Part II</a></h2>
<h3>by Gian Medves<br>
Computer Services Librarian</h3></center>
There is a growing number of Canadian legal resources available on the Internet. Law students can access these resources from the Computer Lab via <b>Netscape</b>  (<b>see <cite>LawLink</cite></b> vol. 1 no. 6 for information on  Netscape), <b>FTP</b>, <b>Turbo Gopher</b> and <b>NCSA Telnet</b>.  
<p>
All of the sites listed below are available through Netscape using the following formats to make the connection:
<ul>	
<li>for a Gopher site, type Gopher:// address
<li>for an FTP site,   type FTP:// address
<li>for a telnet site,  type Telnet://address 
</ul>
They can also be accessed directly, using FTP, Turbo Gopher and NCSA Telnet.  Many of these sites are menu driven.  Follow the menu paths indicated below to locate these resources. 
