<h2><a name = "united">United Nations Human Rights Bibliography on CD-ROM</a></h2>
<h3>By Esther Wan<br>
Coordinator, Information Services</h3></center>
This  bibliography was compiled by the United Nations Library in Geneva in co-operation with the Centre for Human Rights. It contains over 12,000 bibliographic citations to UN documents covering 1980 to October 15, 1993. 
<p>
When selecting the <cite>Human Rights Bibliography</cite> from the main menu of the CD-ROM workstation, the researcher is faced with two choices: to search the complete database, or to pre-select by subject area or type of document. The first option is the most flexible method for the basic researcher. I have tried both methods and frankly speaking, found the pre-selection method very complicated (for some reason, the software does not allow you to create a subset of records as it claims). 
<p>
<h3>Searching</h3>
You can search the database by selecting one or all of the choices from the following list:  all words, title, subject, personal author, corporate author, UN issuing body, session, UN Document symbol, UN sales number or publication date. Once you have completed your search,  the screen will display the number of records that your search has found. Press &lt;enter&gt; and the screen will display a &quot;hitlist&quot; of these items. The hitlist includes the first few words of the title, the date, and the UN document number of each item. To find more detailed information for a particular record, move the cursor down to the record (the citation should turn blue) and press the &lt;Enter&gt; key. This record will  then show the full title of the document, the place and date of publication, the UN document number and the UN Issuing body. 
 <p>
<h3>Navigating</h3>
 The &lt;Escape&gt; key always takes you back a step, &lt;F1&gt; is the HELP key, the &lt;ALT&gt; key allows you use the pull-down command menus, and the &lt;F10&gt; key allows you to quit the program. 
<p>
<h3>Printing</h3>
You can print from this disc four ways:
<ul>
<li>individual records
<li>multiple records (or tagged records)
<li>the hitlist
<li>the search query screen.
</ul>
To print an individual record from the hitlist, move the cursor down to that record and then select the &lt;F7&gt; function key.  The computer will print the full  record for that item.
<p>
To select any of the other three options hit the &lt;ALT&gt; key, then the letter &quot;P&quot; to access the print menu.  You will be given the choice of printing all tagged records, the hitlist and the search query screen.  
<p>
To print full records for some or all of the items found in your search, select &quot;print all tagged records&quot; from the print menu.   Please note,  if you only want to print a few of the records, you must mark the records that you don't want to print.  To do this, you must remove the arrow sign which appears along the left-hand side of the screen by pressing the &lt;spacebar&gt;.  
<p>
To print the hitlist in  brief record format select &quot;hitlist&quot; from the print menu. You can also print the search query screen by selecting that option from the print menu. 
  <p>
This product will save a great deal of time when researching. You can now quickly retrieve relevant references from this compact disc and then find them in the library system using UTCat. 
<p>
<center><img src="../icons/grkban09.gif"></center><p>
