<center><h2><a name = "montreal">University of Montreal Gopher Update</a></h2>
(excerpted from a message on CALL-L)</center>
<P>
 The Centre de Recherche en Droit Public (CRDP) and the Faculty
of Law of the University of Montreal are proud to announce a significant
update of their public resources on the Internet.
<P>
The services now include:
<ul>
<li>the recent rulings of the Supreme Court of Canada (Experimental
Joint Project with the Supreme Court of Canada);
<P>
<li>an important corpus on Quebec Civil Law (Joint Project with
Les Publications du Quebec); doctrinal and other materials of interest to the legal community
such as:
<P>
<li>the Proceedings of conferences pertaining to the legal community,
for instance, the May 1994 Montreal Conference on Electronic Highways;
<P>
<li>&quot;la revue juridique Themis&quot; (U. of M., Faculty
of Law Journal).
</ul>
The Center is  interested in receiving comments on these new electronic
services and is open to collaboration with other institutions.
<P>
CRDP-LAW's database can be accessed via FTP, Gopher and
WWW (Universal Resource Locators below).
<P>
#GSPort=70<br>
#GSPath=<br>
#GSHost=gopher.droit.umontreal.ca
