Circulation Desk at the Bora Laskin Law Library.

<p><center><img src = "../icons/grkban09.gif"></center><p>
<center><h2><a name = "rules">Rules of the Computer Lab</a></h2></center>
<P>
<b>In exchange for access to the computer lab,  law students agree
to comply with the rules and regulations set forth below, and
understand that if found not complying, they will be dismissed
from the lab for the whole term.</b>
<ol>
<li>This Computer Lab is for the sole use of law students. In
order to maintain security and prevent unauthorized use, a combination lock system has
been installed on the Computer Lab door. The combination will be changed periodically.
In order to get  the combination you will have to go to the circulation desk
and sign for it. You will be asked to provide valid ID (student card or library card).
<P>
<li>When in the lab, do not let students in. They must sign for
the combination on their own.
<P>
<li>When in the lab, do not prop the door open as this defeats
the whole purpose of having a secured room.
<P>
<li>If you see anyone who is not a law student using the facility
please report it to the circulation desk.
<P>
<li>Please keep the room as clean and tidy as possible and keep
the noise level down.
<P>
<li>Food and  drinks are not allowed in the Computer Lab.
<P>
<li>Students and faculty are not allowed to:
<ul>
   a) Tamper with systems and/or configurations of computers,
or rearrange desktops.<br>
   b) Make copies or install software on computers.
</ul>
<li>Student files left on the hard drives will be trashed. Make
sure you save your work onto floppy diskettes. This is for your protection as well as
keeping the machines from getting cluttered. A file left on a hard drive can be copied
by someone else.
<P>
<li>The Computer Lab will be reserved at times for classes in
online information retrieval. At these times the lab is reserved for students taking the class.
Computers and printers are not available to any other students at these times. <b>Don't
even ask!</b>
<P>
<li>Printing protocol:
<ul>
<li>Do not print until you have inserted your copy card into
the reader<br>
<li>If you wish to cancel your print job, terminate it from your
workstation; do not simply remove your copy card.
</ul>
</ol>
The Computer Lab is your  facility. Please take care of it. By
following the protocol outlined above we hope to prevent theft
and vandalism and reduce the danger of having viruses invade the
system.

