<li><a name="thirty">G.T. McLaughlin,</a> &quot;On the Periphery of Letter-of-Credit Law: Softening the Rigors of the Strict Compliance&quot;, (1989) 106 <cite>Bank. L.J.</cite> 4, aux pp. 39 et s. Cette th&eacute;orie a m&ecirc;me des &eacute;chos &agrave; l'ext&eacute;rieur des &Eacute;tats-Unis, comme au Br&eacute;sil: L.M. Costa, &quot;Le formalisme dans le cr&eacute;dit documentaire: contestation ou cons&eacute;cration?&quot;, (1993) <cite>R.D.A.I./I.B.L.J.</cite> 707, aux pp. 713 et s.; voir l'analyse de J.F. Dolan, &quot;Letter-of-Credit Dispute Between the Issuer and its Customer: the Issuer's Right under the misnamed Bifurcated Standard&quot;, (1988) 105 <cite>Bank. L.J.</cite> 380, aux pp. 388 et s.



