<li><a name="forty9">En Angleterre:</a> <cite>Deutsche Ruckversicherung AG v. Walbrook Insurance Co. Ltd. et al.</cite>, [1994] 4 All E.R. 181, &agrave; la p. 195 (Q.B.(Com. Ct.)); <cite>The Society of Lloyd's v. Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce et al.</cite>, <i>supra</i>, note 11, &agrave; la p. 580; <cite>Korea Industry Co. Ltd. v. Andoll Ltd.</cite>, [1990] 2 Lloyd's Rep. 183, &agrave; la p. 187 (Singapore C.A.); <cite>United City Merchants (Investments) Ltd. v. Royal Bank of Canada</cite>, <i>supra</i>, note 11, &agrave; la p. 187; R. Jack, <i>supra</i>, note 49, au no 9.11. En France: J. Stoufflet, <i>supra</i>, note 12, au no 120: le professeur Jean Stoufflet nous r&eacute;f&egrave;re &agrave; l'affaire <cite>Angelica</cite>; J. Stoufflet, <i>supra</i>, note 24, aux nos 114 et 115. Aux &Eacute;tats-Unis: Par. 5--114(2) <cite>U.C.C.</cite>; <cite>Sztejn v. J. Henry Schroder Baking Corporation</cite>, <i>supra</i>, note 10, &agrave; la p. 634; <cite>Northwestern Bank v. NFC Financial Corporation</cite>, 365 S.E.2d 14, &agrave; la p. 20 (N.C. App. 1988); <cite>Roman Ceramics Corporation v. Peoples National Bank</cite>, 714 F.2d 1207, &agrave; la p. 1215 (3d Cir. 1983).



