tribunaux interpr&egrave;tent le paragraphe 5--114(2) du <cite>U.C.C.</cite> comme exigeant que le b&eacute;n&eacute;ficiaire soit l'auteur de la fraude ou y ait contribu&eacute;: <cite>Aetna Life &amp; Casualty Company v. Huntington National Park</cite>, 934 F.2d 695, &agrave; la p. 701 (6th Cir. 1991); <cite>Harris Corporation v. National Iranian Radio &amp; Television et al.</cite>, 691 F.2d 1344, &agrave; la p. 1355 (11th Cir. 1982); Note, &quot;`Fraud in the Transaction': Enjoining Letters of Credit during the Iranian Revolution&quot;, (1980) 93 <cite>Harv. L. Rev.</cite> 992, &agrave; la p. 1006.



