<p>
<li><a name="eighty">Ontario, Legislative Assembly,</a> Debates, <cite>Not Yet Healthy, Not Yet Safe</cite> (26 April 1983), E. Martel at 10--12. In one background study of the Royal Commission on New Reproductive Technologies, &quot;Reproductive Hazards in the Workplace: Legal Issues of Regulation, Enforcement, and
Redress,&quot; <i>supra</i> note 5, vol. 4 at 194, J. Fudge and E. Tucker point out that there are only 296 inspectors for 286,000 workplaces in Ontario, and the inspectors' mandate is to facilitate, rather than enforce.
<p>
<li><a name="eighty1">See for example,</a> the <cite>Wilco Canada</cite> and <cite>Mid-western Regional Centre</cite> cases cited in <cite>Not Yet Healthy, Not Yet Safe</cite>, <i>supra</i> note 80 at 12 and 41.
<p>
