<p>
<li><a name="eighty8">See s. 10,</a> <cite>Interpretation Act</cite>, R.S.O. 1990, c. I.11 which provides that: 
<blockquote>
Every Act shall be deemed to be remedial, whether its immediate purport is to direct the doing of anything that the
Legislature deems to be for the public good or to prevent or punish the doing of anything that it deems to be contrary to the public good, and shall accordingly receive such large and liberal construction and interpretation as will best ensure the attainment of the objective of the Act according to its true intent, meaning and spirit.
</blockquote>
