<li><a name="one05">[1979] 1 S.C.R. 183, 92 D.L.R. (3d) 417</a> [hereinafter <cite>Bliss</cite>]. Since this Supreme Court decision, a number of provinces, including Ontario, and the Federal government have enacted amendments clarifying that discrimination on the basis of sex includes pregnancy. A number of Human Rights Tribunals also declined to follow <cite>Bliss</cite> on the grounds that these statements were <i>obiter dicta</i>. See for example: <cite>Tellier-Cohen v. Treasury Board</cite> (1982), 3 C.H.R.R. D/792, aff'd on appeal 4 C.H.R.R. D/1169.
