<p>
<li><a name="one">In 1988,</a> the value of EFT-POS transactions was $256,000. In 1994 the value had increased to $6,787,306,000. Service is now available in British Columbia, Alberta, Saskatchewan, Manitoba, Quebec and the Ottawa area. Interac is in the process of completing its plans for nationwide coverage. Letter of Michelle Hearn, Canadian Payments Association Communications Co-ordinator to author (20 February 1995).
<p>
<li><a name="two">In 1994</a> there were almost 300 million ATM transactions which cleared through the Canadian Payments Association clearing system. This figure does not include transactions which were performed using the machines provided by the account holder's own institution. <i>Ibid.</i>
<p>
<li><a name="three">In 1994,</a> the value of all cheque transactions was $20,953,343,859,000. However, the value of all `small paper items' (essentially cheques under $50,000) was only $1,029,533,926,000. It is the `small paper items' which are more directly comparable to ATM transactions. Again, these figures are for transactions which passed through the Canadian Payments Association clearing system and do not include cheques cleared within the particular institution. <i>Ibid.</i>
