<p>
<li><a name="six">Unless</a> the context clearly indicates otherwise, &quot;bank&quot; refers to the near-banks (trust companies, credit unions, caisses, etc.) as well.
<p>
<li><a name="seven">Bradley Crawford, ed.,</a> <cite>Falconbridge Banking and Bills of Exchange</cite>, 8th ed. (Toronto: Canada Law Book Co., 1986) at 1362--1400 and Ian Baxter, <cite>The Law of Banking</cite> (Toronto: Carswell, 1993) at 19--25 &amp; 58--59, are the two authoritative Canadian treatments of the law in the area of forged cheques.
<p>
