narcotics).
<p>
<li><a name="one45">390 U.S. 377 (1968).</a>  A suitcase had been found at a co-defendant's home, but the defendant claimed possession of the evidence contained within the bag.
<p>
<li><a name ="one46"><cite>Salvucci</cite>,</a> <i>supra</i> note 139 at 90--93. Possession is not sufficient to be a proxy for a legitimate expectation of privacy.
<p>
<li><a name="one47"><i>Ibid</i>. at 90.</a>
