<p>
<li><a name="one06">The intention of Part III</a> of this paper is to provide an overview of the tax rules relating to REITs. An in-depth analysis of the rules dealing with taxation of trusts is beyond the scope of this paper.
<p>
<li><a name="one07">The differences in the tax</a> treatment between an open-end and closed-end REIT structure will be eliminated by the rules newly proposed by Revenue Canada. The proposed changes to the
<cite>Income Tax Act</cite> are discussed in Part III(6) of this paper.
<p>
<li><a name="one08">The tax rules relating to unit</a> trusts and mutual fund trusts are contained in Part III(3) of this paper.
<p>
<li><a name="one09">The tax</a> rules relating to commercial trusts are contained in Part III(2) of this paper.
<p>
<li><a name="one10">Orlando REIT Prospectus,</a> <i>supra</i> note 55 at 4.
<p>
