<p>
<li><a name="one13">The REIT appears</a> to be hoping that sometime in the next year the Department of Finance will introduce amended legislation to permit a closed-end real estate fund to qualify as a mutual fund trust.
<p>
<li><a name="one14">The recent proposals by Revenue</a> Canada to amend provisions of the <cite>Income Tax Act</cite> (discussed in Part III(6)), should make issuers indifferent, from a tax perspective, as to what structure (open-end or closed-end) is selected.
<p>
<li><a name="one15">Young,</a> <i>supra</i> note 4 at 15.
