<li><a name="fifty8"><cite>Air Canada</cite>,</a> <i>supra</i> note 21 at 1203: &quot;The law of restitution is not intended to provide windfalls to plaintiffs who have suffered no loss. Its function is to ensure that where a plaintiff has been deprived of wealth that is either in his possession or would have accrued for his benefit, it is
