<li><a name="forty3">In <cite>Eastmain Band v. Canada</cite>,</a> [1993] 3 C.N.L.R. 55 (F.C.A.) [hereinafter <cite>Eastmain</cite>], D&eacute;cary J. concluded that Eastmain 1 Project was part of the Complexe La Grande in 1975, which was exempt from environmental assessment because it was not an addition, a substantial modification, or a new project anticipated in the <cite>JBNQA</cite>, <i>supra</i> note 3 at 8.1.2, 8.1.3. The parties had foreseen the construction of the Eastmain Dam, although there was very little research completed, progress made, or discussion of the project when the <cite>JBNQA</cite> was signed in 1975. The Quebec
Government is now required to suspend the transportation of produced hydroelectric power to the U.S. until an environmental assessment of the operation has been completed. See <cite>Quebec v. Canada</cite>, [1994] S.C.J. No. 13 (Q.L).
