<li><a name="seventy1"><i>Supra</i> note 21.</a> The Inuvialuit and the Gwich'in are in the process of negotiating with the Territorial government for regional self-government. Interestingly, 1999 has been proclaimed as the deadline for such an arrangement in light of the Nunavut division from the Northwest Territories which will relegate aboriginals in the Western Arctic to a minority politically. Yukon Indians have an outlined framework of
discussion for self-government but there is still no obligation on the government as to when negotiations will commence. See Canada, Department of Indian Affairs and Northern Development, <cite>Champagne and Aishihik: First Nations Final Agreement</cite> (Ottawa: Minister of Supplies and Services, 1993) s. 24.
