<p>
<li><a name="ninety5">The classification</a> of Nunavut as a Territory or another province is a subject of much debate. Besides the constitutional difficulties emerging from the creation of a new province, there is no legal authority to support the emergence of a province out of a Territory. For further discussion see Purich, <i>supra</i> note 2 at 89; Merritt &amp; Fenge, <i>supra</i> note 6; Dacks, <i>supra</i> note 21; G. Robertson, <cite>Northern Provinces: A Mistaken Goal</cite> (Montreal: Institute for Research on Public Policy, 1985).
