<li><a name="one35">The presumption</a> that ecological interests will surrender to economic development is
questionable. In the Western Arctic, the Inuvialuit Environmental Impact Review Board rejected the Kulluk Drilling Program in the Beaufort Sea because its proposal outlining its response for the worst case scenario (a possible well blowout) was inadequate. Allowing the project may have injected more money into the Inuvialuit economy, but the Environmental Impact Review Board preferred to delay the project until all ecological concerns, present and future, were assuaged.
