<li><a name="one60">M.H. Redish &amp; G. Lippman,</a> &quot;Freedom of Expression and the Civic Republican Revival in Constitutional Theory: The Ominous Implications&quot; (1991) 79 Cal. L. Rev. 267 at 310. But see G. Henley, &quot;Preferences About Preferences: A Positive Justification for Canadian Content Regulation&quot; (1993) 3 M.C.L.R. 127.
